  "acceptance_criteria": [
    "Turn the appointment/governance UI from debug form/table behavior into a player flow for office selection, candidate comparison, eligible/rejected explanation, impact preview, confirmation, and result feedback.",
    "Bulk preview may remain available but must not dominate the primary player flow or bypass the preview-confirm-result pattern.",
    "Reason-code display strings are localized in the UI layer, while raw reason codes remain available only through explicit dev/debug affordances.",
    "The flow uses existing read models, command builders, previews, and rejection results; it must not duplicate appointment formulas or write domain state directly.",
    "Player and AI command parity remains intact: UI submits the same GameCommand surface and does not introduce player-only hidden behavior.",
    "Storybook and Playwright cover English, Simplified Chinese, eligible, rejected, empty, confirm, result, debug-hidden, and no-overlap states."
  ],
